      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": null,
      "message": "These parameters are to talk to Guard PDP.   It doesn't do healthchecks.   It just happened that the username that the new components use is \"healthcheck\".  \n\nThe idea is that we support either the legacy or PAP for guards.   If somebody wants to enable legacy instead of \"new\".    They'll come here and will put back the old values and will interact with legacy.\n\nI'm just trying to avoid to support 2 PAPs/PDPs settings double configuration at the same time.",
      "author": {
